<!DOCTYPE ui:UiBinder SYSTEM "http://dl.google.com/gwt/DTD/xhtml.ent">
<ui:UiBinder xmlns:ui="urn:ui:com.google.gwt.uibinder" xmlns:g="urn:import:com.google.gwt.user.client.ui">
  <ui:style>
    .important {
    	font-weight: bold;
    }
  </ui:style>
  <g:HTMLPanel>
    <g:SimplePanel ui:field="placeholder" />

    <p>With the stack plugin, you can have Flot stack the
      series. This is useful if you wish to display both a total and
      the
      constituents it is made of. The only requirement is that you provide
      the input sorted on x.</p>

    <p class="stackControls">
      <g:CheckBox ui:field="stacking" text="Stacking" value="true"/>
    </p>

    <p class="graphControls">
      <g:RadioButton ui:field="bars" text="Bars" name="graphControls" value="true"/>
      <g:RadioButton ui:field="lines" text="Lines" name="graphControls" />
      <g:RadioButton ui:field="linesStep" text="Lines with steps" name="graphControls" />
    </p>
  </g:HTMLPanel>
</ui:UiBinder>